### Get Products
GET http://localhost:4004/admin/Products

###

### Get Suppliers
GET http://localhost:4004/admin/Suppliers

###

### Get Customers
GET http://localhost:4004/admin/Customers

###

### Get Sales Orders
GET http://localhost:4004/sales/SalesOrders

###

### Expand Customer
GET http://localhost:4004/sales/SalesOrders?$expand=customer

###

### Expand Product in Items
GET http://localhost:4004/admin/SalesOrderItems?$expand=product

###

### Filter Products
GET http://localhost:4004/admin/Products?$filter=price gt 1000

###

### Order By Price
GET http://localhost:4004/admin/Products?$orderby=price desc

###

### Product Catalog Report
GET http://localhost:4004/reports/ProductCatalog

###

### Low Stock Alert
GET http://localhost:4004/reports/LowStockAlert

###

### Order Report
GET http://localhost:4004/reports/OrderReport

###

### Deep Insert Sales Order
POST http://localhost:4004/sales/SalesOrders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderNumber": "SO2001",
  "customer_ID": "cus1",
  "orderDate": "2026-06-05",
  "totalAmount": 1600,
  "currency_code": "INR",
  "status": "Created",
  "items": [
    {
      "product_ID": "prd3",
      "quantity": 2,
      "unitPrice": 800,
      "netAmount": 1600
    }
  ]
}

### ===================================================================
@sales = http://localhost:4004/sales

### Test 1: Create order without customer (should fail)
POST {{sales}}/SalesOrders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderDate": "2026-06-15",
  "items": [
    {
      "product_ID": "prd1",
      "quantity": 2,
      "unitPrice": 55000
    }
  ]
}

### Test 2: Create order with past date (should fail)
POST {{sales}}/SalesOrders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_ID": "cus1",
  "orderDate": "2020-01-01",
  "items": [
    {
      "product_ID": "prd1",
      "quantity": 2,
      "unitPrice": 55000
    }
  ]
}

### Test 3: Create order with invalid item (quantity 0)
POST {{sales}}/SalesOrders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_ID": "cus1",
  "orderDate": "2026-06-15",
  "items": [
    {
      "product_ID": "prd1",
      "quantity": 0,
      "unitPrice": 55000
    }
  ]
}

### Test 4: Create valid order
POST {{sales}}/SalesOrders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_ID": "cus1",
  "orderNumber": "SO2001",
  "orderDate": "2026-06-15",
  "currency_code": "INR",
  "items": [
    {
      "product_ID": "prd1",
      "quantity": 2,
      "unitPrice": 55000
    },
    {
      "product_ID": "prd3",
      "quantity": 2,
      "unitPrice": 800
    }
  ]
}



### Test 5: Try invalid status transition (New → Delivered should fail)
PATCH {{sales}}/SalesOrders(ORDER-ID-FROM-TEST-4)
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "Delivered"
}

### Test 6: Valid status transition (New → Confirmed)
PATCH {{sales}}/SalesOrders(bc90c0e2-d744-4d7d-8570-4903e03ad180)
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "Delivered"
}

### Test 6: Valid status transition (should succeed)

PATCH {{sales}}/SalesOrders(bc90c0e2-d744-4d7d-8570-4903e03ad180)
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "Confirmed"
}
